F:

Your Beauty lies in Contradiction. Controversial, unpredictable, and
never what anyone expects. You appearance and your personality are two
opposite things. Even your appearance sends different signals to different
people. To some you may look innocent and sweet, to others you look mysterious
and intimidating at the same time. No one ever knows what to expect with you.
You are a little bit of everything all mixed together. You can be watching
the football game with the guys one minute and the next out shopping at the
mall. You seem to be almost a different person every time you meet someone, but
at the same time you know exactly who you are and there is always that one
thing that makes you you. You enjoy keeping people guessing and people love how
completely unpredictable you are.

B:

You take the Road Less
Traveled. Who wants to go where everyone else has already gone
anyway? You look for the hidden paths, ones most don't see and don't care to
venture down. You go boldly and stand proud discontent with what's been put in
front of you, determined to find a way perfect for you even no one else will take it
with you. You live as you want and not for others, but be careful not become
selfish. Others may need you and you should be there for them, especially the
ones close to you. You tend to be the leader in most situations and people listen
and trust you not lead them astray. Your firm in your opinions and beliefs and
unwilling to change yourself to suit other people. By the same token, you can be
stubborn to a fault, change isn't always a bad thing you know. Everyone changes
and grows, you shouldn't try to stay exactly the same or you could be left
behind. Then again, you may change frequently. Some people change to fit in, you my
little non-conformist, may change to be set apart. It's great to be different,
but it's also just as great to have things in common with people, even if those
people are in that "crowd" you seem to have a vendetta against. Don't try to
be different, just be who you are, whoever that is and you'll be unique all on
your own. So make some time for people, let yourself blend into the crowd every
once in awhile, you may just learn something about them and yourself you never
knew before.

Long time since I updated....mainly cause nothing important has happened, until last night :D.

Yesterday around 1-2ish my brother and I went to his new girlfriend's house and we hung out for a while, but it was fun cause his girlfriend is my age and is one of my old friends.  Then around 5 we went over to the church to help put up that stuff on the floors, I dunno what it's called, it's the stuff that goes around the edge of the floor where the wall meets the floor.....yeah, that stuff.  But nobody was there yet so we went back to Rachel's house (friend person).  Then around 6 we went back over and laid out all the crap we were supposed to and went back to Rachel's house.  Then we just chilled over there for a while and Rachel's brother came home.  (Now for a little bit of backround, Rachel's brother and Bobby (my bro) used to be really great friends, like brothers, but Rachel's bro started to be obsessed with FFXI and couldn't talk about anything but that, which is sad.  Then when Bobby and Rachel started going out and her brother wanted to hang out with Bobby, he (rachel's bro) would get really pissed because Rachel would come along with them.  Rachel's brother is such a hypocrite however, because when he and bobby would hang out, he'd bring his girlfriend.....tell me how much sense that makes. -_-  So, back to the story :p.)  When Rachel's brother came home with his friend Travis, who is really tall and hot *drools*, he asked if Bobby was coming to the movies and Bobby said yeah and that Rachel was coming too, that made Rachel's brother really mad.  So then Rachel's brother yelled at Rachel, whined to his mom, and left the house without even talking to Bobby.  They went to see Alien VS Predator at 9:30, so we were still able to get into the theater without them seeing us :).  Oh yeah, Rachel's friend Andrea (a different one) was there the whole time, it's really weird, me and her are mostly the same, except she's a smoker and....I'm not....anymore.... <.<   >.>

Anyway, Andrea didn't feel like going to the movies so we dropped her off on our way to the movies and went and saw Collateral.  It was an interesting movie, I guess.  After it was over, around 1am today we went back to Rachel's house and Rachel and I chilled upstairs while Bobby went downstairs where Rachel's bro and Travis were.  I'm not sure what they played, but I remember that Rachel and I were watching the Olympics and decided to drink some beer, because her mom doesn't really care what they do, it's great, her mom was asleep on the couch right across from us xD.  I had this blue thing that came in a bottle, it was like blue raspberry candy with liquor x.x  it was gross, but yummy all at once.  It burned on the way down though :/.  Now keep in mind, I'm not an alcoholic in anyway, I'm not even a drinker really, and considering I weigh nothing (-_-) it doesn't take me much to get tipsy.  So Rachel and Bobby went out onto the porch or something and Rachel's brother and Travis would walk by every so often to refresh their beer supply, while I laid on the couch and watched the olympics.  I sort of remember staring at Travis when he walked by, cause he's really tall and I remember thinking that he must get special made clothes or something.  Then I realized he was wearing one of those shirts guys wear that are like, a size too small or something and so it barely covered the tops of his pants, I was hoping it'd fall off :D.  Then I 'took a nap' and woke up around 3 when Bobby and Rachel were saying their goodbyes.  So I got up and wobbled to the car and fell down some stairs x.x  I think we got home about...3:30 or something and I went up to bed and just kinda dozed off before my head hit the pillow.

Then this morning I woke up and I think I'm having a hang over -_- or something, I slept through my alarm and woke up with a headache and my chest hurt.  I guess that's what a hangover feels like, but the only other time I've actually gotten drunk was when I played beer pong in our basement with my brother and one of his ex-gfs and I passed out watching Harry Potter, good times, good times...

Ok....well...I think that's all that happened, if I am told I did something stupid or anything weird happened, I'll be sure to let you all know :).
Lesson of this update: It doesn't take much to get me drunk, that's a hint for all my loverly stalkers ;)

Alright, now I'm bored again.....dum dee dum. Someone take some tests or something xD.  I need to steal them and take them and such.

I mean he wasn't the worst but he deffinetly wasn't the best either.  The only reason he is getting this treatment is because he was the president.  If I were president, which I won't be because (hate to say it) nobody will ever elect a female president, I wouldn't want my casket on display where everyone can come up and look at it.

Why do people wait in line for hours to see some casket for like 10 seconds.  I could understand if it was a roller coaster or an amusement park ride or something, but dead guy....no way.  One of my friends was telling me about how their dad was trying to get them to go and see it and she told him, "If you wanna go see it that badly shut up and go look, I'll be here when you get back."  That's how I feel...whenever I turn on the news I see his face and I'm like...."ROAR!"

The media, ah... the media, how they love to take these stories and blow them up into something so big it's there wherever you turn around.  Every news channel I've seen has his face plastered to the screen and are showing the excact same footage from a different angle.  Makes me imagine someone flipping from one news channel to the other to see all sides of the casket. xD That would be funny to watch someone decide which channel is getting a better view of the dead guy.

Alright, I think I'm gonna stop now before I go insane.  It's been fun :B

I had a weird dream last night....I was walking down the street of my neighborhood and it was lined with more trees than usual and there was this new driveway.  Then I was at the driveway looking at the house and it was a huge mansion, which looked really cool. Suddenly I was at the door and there was this kid talking to me about something and for some reason we jumped from the ground, three stories to the roof.  After that we ran around and I was running like...really fast, then the kids family came out and they were monsters or wanted to kill me or something and so I ran down their driveway and down a big hill to the next court and hid there for a few minutes.  But I found myself wanting to go back to the mansion and so I did and found the kid again and he invited me inside so I went in and we played in his house for a while.  The family turned all the power off in the house and shut all the windows or something and tried to find where we had gone.  So it was like playing hide and seek... Well today started off bad, I was running late getting up and I figured that I should've stayed in bed, I was right.  My school day started off good, I found out a friend had died in a car accident, not a best friend but we did hang out occasionally.  Then I went to History, depressed, and got to finish a movie about all of the dead people in the holocaust and my teacher made fun of me when I knew the answer to his question.  Teacher, "What was the name of Hitler's 'supirior race?"  Me, "Aryan(sp??)"  Teacher, "Yes, good thing andrea knows so much, considering she's part of it..."  Me, "*shakes head and pretends to cry*"  Teacher, "I was just kidding"  Me, "Whatever."  Oh yeah, can't forget about the football player that threw trash into the hood of my hoodie. :(
On to Latin :/....the teacher wasn't there, we had to translate an entire page out of our books, talk about frickin boring!
Now right through finance, it was just boring, and on to english, we go new seats.  They suck....blah....I miss my old seat which was in a row of like three people, compared to everyone else's rows of 5 people, the teacher would always forget about us.  It was nice.  Oh how I miss that seat.
Lunch, my friends, or so they were called before lunch today, decided to make fun of me and draw a big penis on my science binder.....I ripped the cover off, took my trash and found someone else to hang out with for the rest of lunch, I haven't talked to my 'friends' since.
Keyboarding/studyhall, FUCKING RETARDED, what a waste of a class.
Math...my teacher hates me, and so I made a joke today, and she just got even more pissed at me.  The class laughed, which was kinda nice.  Anyway....
Science, our teacher finally came back from being sick, we had like a chapter of busy work each day, what a waste.  Now that he's back he gives us this hard work...(sarcasm).  We're to copy 12 words and make note cards, due tomorrow at the end of class.....I copied the words and read more of The Silver Kiss.
So one might think that my day couldn't get any worse, but OH NO I find a way to make it worse!  I came home to find my house locked....me without a key, OF COURSE!!!  I sat outside from 2:30 to 4:30 in the mid 40's, oh and on top of that, the wind decided it was a nice day to blow in every possible direction.  It doesn't sound that bad after the winter we had, but with no way to warm myself up it frickin sucked.  I went for a walk through the woods and tried not to freeze to death and I tried reading my book but I gave up because I was FRICKIN COLD!!!  So I fell asleep on my porch, next to a flower pot, using my bookbag as a pillow and all curled up inside my hoodie, I was hidden from the world.  It was kinda nice, if it wasn't so cold.  I woke up cause I felt the garage door open, or heard it, not sure, my senses were frozen.  I went inside with my daddy and he made me hot chocolate and I curled up on the couch in my sleeping bag and tried to warm myself up.  Then he decided to yell at me because I had forgotten all of my stuff at home, my keys and such.  So I suggested that he start leaving a key outside and he just told me to shut it and lectured me about how unsafe it was.
Later my mommy came home, around 5ish and I heard her knock, then I got up to get the door and she was unlocking it and she looked at me and said, well thanks for making me wait out here in the cold so long for you to open the door.  That set me off, so I was like "Don't talk to me about being frickin cold!  I got locked out of the house today and sat here for 2 hours freezing my butt off."  All she said was, awww I'm sorry, and My poor baby....today sucked, I can't wait to go to sleep and get this awful day over with......
